f=Executive Office/echo/custom/pitch-narrative/SKILL.md · in=pitch-narrative maintains versioned pitch story whatever business it's serving fixed template, repeatable process building, adapting, tracking one coherent narrative over time. story itself (problem, solution, traction, ask) never invented assumed skill; it's always sourced actual business profile operator provides already exists prior use skill. · p=Prevent pitch story drifting reinvented scratch time new pitch needed. Give echo consistent process adapting one underlying narrative whichever pitch type audience front it, while keeping record what changed why. · wu=Triggers: "investor deck" (narrative input pitch-framework), "pitch update," "fundraise narrative," "adapt pitch [audience]," any time underlying business story needs restated new context. · st:/ Protocol=`Establish or load the business profile (never assumed) \· -> Determine pitch type (investor / partnership / customer-facing) \· -> Determine audience tier within that type \· -> Adapt narrative depth and framing accordingly \· -> Version the output; log what changed from the last version` · h3:Phase Establish Business Profile=Before writing any narrative, get (or load, already established prior run) actual business profile: · h3:Phase Establish Business Profile=**Problem**: what pain point, quantified possible., **Solution wedge**: what business it's right entry point., **Traction**: real metrics, customers, milestones never invented., **Ask**: what's requested (funding amount, partnership terms, etc.), known yet. · h3:Phase Establish Business Profile=any missing vague, ask draft narrative around guess. profile source truth version narrative follows. · h3:Phase Determine Pitch Type=Ask which applies (this match whichever structure `pitch-framework` use downstream, deck built): · h3:Phase Determine Pitch Type=**Investor pitch** narrative center market size, business model, now., **Partnership proposal** narrative center mutual benefit partner specifically., **Customer-facing** narrative center customer's pain point proof it's solved. · h3:Phase Determine Audience Tier=Within pitch type, ask (or infer context confirm) audience tier: · h3:Phase Determine Audience Tier=investor pitches: **angel** (simpler, faster, founder-story-forward) **VC** (fuller, market-sizing business-model-forward) **strategic investor** (emphasis strategic fit their portfolio/business)., partnership proposals: tier much context partner already (cold outreach vs. warm relationship)., customer-facing: tier buyer sophistication (technical buyer vs. business buyer). · h3:Phase Adapt Draft=Using business profile Phase draft narrative depth framing match Phase Phase · h3:Phase Adapt Draft=Pull latest metrics wherever operator says they're tracked (don't assume source ask unclear)., Keep underlying facts identical across versions depth, framing, emphasis change audience, never facts themselves. · h3:Phase Version Log=Save output new version within skill's working file (e.g. `pitch-narrative-log.md`, created first use), with: · h3:Phase Version Log=date, pitch type, audience tier version., brief note what changed last version type/tier (new traction numbers, adjusted ask, repositioned wedge, etc.)., full narrative text version. · h3:Phase Version Log=local, self-contained version log dependent any external memory system. · of=`## Pitch Narrative — [pitch type] / [audience tier] — [date] \·  \· ### What Changed Since Last Version (same type/tier) \· [Delta notes, or "first version" if none exists yet] \· ` · pr=narrative never invented independently business profile profile stale missing pieces, say rather filling gaps generic pitch language., Facts stay constant across audience adaptations framing depth change. Changing actual numbers claims between angel version credibility risk, feature., Version everything never silently overwrite prior narrative version without logging what changed. · f=business profile exists yet, skill's first job establishing one (Phase don't skip drafting., operator doesn't know audience tier yet, ask rather defaulting detailed (VC) version, since over-explaining angel under-explaining cost credibility., metrics can't sourced, flag exactly which numbers missing rather drafting around them vague language. · b:with Other echo Skills=pitch-narrative owns **story**; `pitch-framework` owns **slides/structure**. building deck, pitch-framework pull current canonical narrative (matching pitch type) rather drafting narrative independently., `investor-update-template` (not built) separate, recurring artifact (monthly/quarterly progress) distinct skill's one-off/occasional pitch narrative, though stay factually consistent other.